PROGRAMMING PRACTICES

1. No changes to the database fields must be made without discussing it.
2. All settings (including database settings) must be put in the settings file. Nothing should be hardcoded.Like even coefficients for the algorithm.
3. Names of variables must reflect its purpose.
4. Commenting is compulsory.
5. Indentation is compulsory
6. Form validation is compulsory.

Use filter_var($str, FILTER_SANITIZE_STRING);
  $data = trim($data);
  $data = stripslashes($data);
  $data = htmlspecialchars($data);
  
  
7. All objects should be accessed using their id, not any other attribute like name (like for UPDATE statements)
8. Do not push broken versions.
